      {
        "id": 2599578,
        "name": "Markus S",
        "username": "Markus_S",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/markus_s/{size}/1235_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-03-11T11:41:58.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"150530\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>2017 Dauvissat Sechet<br>\nThis nose have I never experienced in a Davissat 1er Cru.<br>\nA lot of fruit and flowery fragrances. No salt\u2026<br>\nAnd the taste lacks totally the briney character of previous vintages. Reminds me more of a Raveneau 1er Cru<br>\nWill the wine change? Lets see over the next decades</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Can\u2019t answer you because they are out of my price range now ($100+/bottle), but a 2002 Sechets opened this weekend was pure class and lively as ever, salty tang included!</p>",
